transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Biagra, this is Charles.

Speaker 2: Yes, I was calling about my prescription.

Speaker 1: And I was told when I originally got the prescription—

Speaker 2: That it was not an automatic renewal.

Speaker 1: Every however many months.

Speaker 2: And then I see I get a notice from my bank—

Speaker 1: That you guys took $163 out of my account.

Speaker 2: Okay, Michael Eads in Enumclaw, Washington.

Speaker 1: Correct.

Speaker 2: Gotcha, okay, so I'm not sure who you spoke with—

Speaker 1: That said that these things don't come with refills—

Speaker 2: But they definitely do.

Speaker 1: So if you don't need them—

Speaker 2: What you're gonna do when they arrive—

Speaker 1: Is write "return to sender" on the package—

Speaker 2: Don't rip it up or do anything to it.

Speaker 1: Throw it back in the mailbox—

Speaker 2: Mailman will come by and take it—

Speaker 1: Send it right back to us—

Speaker 2: And then we'll issue a refund for you, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right, and then everything going forward—

Speaker 1: Will be canceled as well.

Speaker 2: Okay, perfect, yeah, I don't need them that often.

Speaker 1: I didn't, like I said, when I signed up—

Speaker 2: They said it wasn't renewal, that's why I signed up.

Speaker 1: I thought, oh, okay, well, I'll just use them—

Speaker 2: As I need them kind of a deal.

Speaker 1: Yeah, yeah, so I mean—

Speaker 2: We are definitely customer service friendly—

Speaker 1: But yeah, understandably so—

Speaker 2: That you got 80 pills the first time.

Speaker 1: So yeah, just call us—

Speaker 2: And then call us back and let us know—

Speaker 1: Next time you need them—

Speaker 2: And then we can talk about different quantities—

Speaker 1: And prices if you don't need the 40 pills all at once—

Speaker 2: All right?

Speaker 1: Right, well, that's why I bought 80—

Speaker 2: You know, to begin with.

Speaker 1: Well, that'll last me, you know—

Speaker 2: A year or whatever.

Speaker 1: Exactly, exactly, yeah.

Speaker 2: So I understand, just give us a call, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, so when the package comes—

Speaker 2: Just write "return to sender" and put it in the mailbox.

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: Okay, sounds good.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Sounds good, yes, sir, have a great one.

Speaker 1: Bye.
